<para>This function does the same thing as <ref refid="group__group__funcmacro__dialog_1ga6d8198c95b97786f206abfde010a4d8f" kindref="member">wxAboutBox()</ref> except that it always uses the generic wxWidgets version of the dialog instead of the native one. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This is mainly useful if you need to customize the dialog by e.g. adding custom controls to it (customizing the native dialog is not currently supported).</para><para>See the <ref refid="page_samples_1page_samples_dialogs" kindref="member">Dialogs Sample</ref> for an example of about dialog customization.</para><para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classwx_about_dialog_info" kindref="compound">wxAboutDialogInfo</ref></para></simplesect>
Include file:<linebreak/>
